<paragraph blockId="7.[136,1452,356,558]" box="[136,1097,356,378]" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">
Etymology:—Latin “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="N. K. Zeng, Y. X. Han &amp; Zhi Q. Liang" authorityYear="2022" box="[341,456,356,377]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Russulaceae" genus="Russula" kingdom="Fungi" order="Russulales" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="hainanensis">
<emphasis box="[341,456,356,377]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">hainanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” refers to the new species being found in 
<collectingRegion box="[860,1023,356,378]" country="China" name="Hainan" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">Hainan Province</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1033,1093,356,378]" name="China" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">China</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[136,1452,356,558]" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">
Diagnosis:—Differs from closest species of 
<emphasis box="[556,571,392,413]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">R</emphasis>
. sect. 
<taxonomicName box="[630,713,392,413]" genus="Heterophyllidia" pageId="7" pageNumber="48" rank="section" section="Ingratae">
<emphasis box="[630,713,392,413]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">Ingratae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by a pileus covered with large, brown to reddish brown patches; a pale yellow stipe with pale brown to brown granules; basidiospores with subreticulate ornamentation 0.3–0.6 μm high, and an association with trees of 
<taxonomicName box="[267,438,464,486]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Dipterocarpaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Dipterocarpaceae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
